## ☕ Core Java Practice

From **31 May 2026 to 2 June 2026**, I spent time getting comfortable with the basics of Java and understanding how programming logic works. Instead of rushing through topics, I focused on learning concepts step by step and practicing them through code.

During this time, I worked with **data types, variables, operators, conditional statements, and loops**. I tried to understand not just *what* the code does, but *why* it works that way. This helped me build a stronger foundation in Java.

I also practiced creating different **star and number patterns**, which improved my understanding of nested loops and problem-solving. These exercises taught me how to break a problem into smaller steps and think more logically while coding.

This was the beginning of my Java journey and an important step toward learning **Data Structures & Algorithms and Backend Development**. The goal was simple: build strong fundamentals before moving on to more advanced topics.

